l Men's Club World Championship]]<ref>{{cite web|title=Team Roster \u2013 Trentino Diatec|url=http://www.fivb.org/en/volleyball/Competitions/ClubWorldChampionships/men/2013/Teams.asp?Team=TRE|work=clubworldchampionships.2012.men.fivb.com|date= |accessdate=3 January 2016}}</ref>. Since November 2018 he plays for the Polish club [[Aluron Virtu CMC Zawiercie]] in [[PlusLiga]].\n\n==Sporting achievements==\n* '''[[FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|FIVB Club World Championship]]'''\n** [[File:Bronze medal world centered-2.svg|16px]] [[2013 FIVB Volleyball Men's Club World Championship|Brazil 2013]], with [[Trentino Volley|Diatec Trentino]] \n\n* '''National championships'''\n** '''2011/2012''' [[File:Gold medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Portuguese Volleyball First Division|Portuguese Championship]], with [[S.C. Espinho (volleyball)|SC Espinho]] \n** '''2013/2014''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] Italian SuperCup, with [[Trentino Volley|Diatec Trentino]] \n** '''2014/2015''' [[File:Bronze medal with cup.svg|16px]] [[Turkish Men's Volleyball League|Turkish Championship]], with [[Ziraat Bankasi Ankara|Ziraat Bankasi]]\n\n* '''National team'''\n** '''2018''' [[File:Simple gold cup.svg|16px]] [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Challenger Cup|FIVB Challenger Cup]]\n\n===Individually===\n* '''2018:''' [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Challenger Cup|FIVB Challenger Cup]] \u2013 The Best Server\n* '''2018:''' [[2018 FIVB Volleyball Men's Challenger Cup|FIVB Challenger Cup]] \u2013 The Best Spiker\n\n==References==\n<references/>\n\n==External links==\n* [http://aluronvirtu.pl/team/alexandre-ferreira/ profile] at ''AluronVirtu.pl''\n* [http://www.plusliga.pl/players/id/30579 profile] at ''PlusLiga.pl''\n* [http://www.legavolley.it/player/FER-ALE-91 profile] at ''LegaVolley.it''\n* [http://www.volleyball-movies.net/alexandre-ferreira-p964 profile] at ''Volleyball-Movies.net''\n* [http://worldleague.2017.fivb.com/en/group2/teams/por-portugal/players/alexandre-ferreira?id=56815 prof